wikipedia_page.main: Calaum Jahraldo-Martin (born 27 April 1993) is an Antigua and Barbuda international footballer who plays as a defender.

response: On 21 January 2016, Nolan was announced as the player-manager of Leyton Orient, signing a -year deal with the club. Two days later, he won his first match as manager in League Two, 2–0 at Wycombe Wanderers, with himself as an unused substitute. On 26 January, against Newport County at Brisbane Road, he made his debut in the 79th minute for Calaum Jahraldo-Martin, and sent in the cross from which the O's won a penalty kick which Jay Simpson converted for the only goal of the game. He made his first start for the club in the away game against Portsmouth on 6 February, where he played 70 minutes in a 1-0 victory for Leyton Orient.
